questions.

29:17.655 --> 29:19.724 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
They're pushing the envelope.

29:19.758 --> 29:25.864 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And they're asking the questions
that I have,
that are aligned with my views.

29:25.897 --> 29:30.502 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JOHN YANG: Huey, the Republican,
is a retired
small business owner.

29:30.535 --> 29:34.806 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
He and his wife, Lorri (ph),
view the world
through a very different news
prism.

29:34.839 --> 29:40.345 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARCUS HUEY: I try to get up a
little bit
before 7:00 -- 7:00, I'm in the
breakfast

29:40.378 --> 29:41.346 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
room.

29:41.379 --> 29:43.214 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I have FOX News on.

29:43.248 --> 29:49.020 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I have The Wall Street Journal
down in front
of me, and then I have my iPhone
next to me.

29:49.053 --> 29:54.392 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And if there's no breaking,
urgent news on
the TV, then the first thing I
do is, I will

29:54.425 --> 30:00.732 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
go check my phone, and look
through my Facebook
wall to see anything that I
might have missed

30:00.765 --> 30:02.500 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
through the night.

30:02.534 --> 30:06.004 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JOHN YANG: You said whatever you
