39:16.654 --> 39:22.493 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Hey, even Southwest is now under
pressure
to impose fees to increase
profits.

39:22.526 --> 39:27.565 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In justifying the profits of Aer
Lingus, which
itself has merged with British
Airways and

39:27.598 --> 39:34.305 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Iberia, CEO Kavanagh might as
well be speaking
for the industry as a whole: It
has achieved

39:34.338 --> 39:35.673 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
greater efficiency.

39:35.706 --> 39:41.145 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, your story is: We finally
figured out
how to do it right.

39:41.178 --> 39:42.680 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Is that true?

39:42.713 --> 39:44.915 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
STEPHEN KAVANAGH: We have
figured out what
you need to manage.

39:44.949 --> 39:46.784 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
KEVIN DILLON, Executive
Director, Connecticut
Airport Authority: Airlines are
extremely

39:46.817 --> 39:48.552 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
