commercial risk into
launching a route.

40:26.991 --> 40:30.060 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The fact that they would share
some of the
risk, we think is totally fair.

40:30.094 --> 40:34.865 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
PAUL SOLMAN: Aer Lingus
spokesman Declan Kearney
stressed that the company too is
making an

40:34.899 --> 40:40.738 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
