loneliness.

50:48.912 --> 50:51.281 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
There's this comic book
character named Monica.

50:51.314 --> 50:53.550 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It was a constant that I had in
my life.

50:53.583 --> 50:56.019 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I could read stories about
Monica and her
friends.

50:56.053 --> 51:00.490 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I thought that if I grew up and
I could do
that for another child, like,
that would be

51:00.524 --> 51:08.965 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
worthwhile.

51:08.999 --> 51:12.235 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I definitely feel that I wasn't
seen when
I was a child.

51:12.269 --> 51:15.238 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
When I moved to the U.S., I
didn't have a
voice.

51:15.272 --> 51:17.207 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
English was difficult for me to
speak.

51:17.240 --> 51:20.744 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
That was when I really connected
with the
value of art and expression.

51:20.777 --> 51:26.550 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There is a sense of wanting to
find belonging
when you have experiences of
being an outsider,

51:26.583 --> 51:32.622 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and wanting to create something
that feels
really true to yourself,because
you're constantly

51:32.656 --> 51:36.026 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
comparing yourself to something
else, and
it doesn't quite match.

51:36.059 --> 51:41.531 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The process of creating from the
inside out,
it's really a process of
mattering.

51:41.565 --> 51:46.403 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
When I teach, a lot of students
ask me like,
what do you use, what is your
tool, and stuff

51:46.436 --> 51:47.404 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
like that.

51:47.437 --> 51:48.438 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
It goes much deeper than that.

51:48.472 --> 51:50.040 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
It goes into, like, who are you?

51:50.073 --> 51:51.708 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
What do you actually want to
say?

51:51.741 --> 51:53.310 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
What matters to you?

51:53.343 --> 51:55.512 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
From that place, everything is
possible.

51:55.545 --> 51:57.314 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
You will find a way to get it
out.

51:57.347 --> 52:01.084 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
One of the best things that I
things that
I do with the kids is that I
say, let's all

52:01.118 --> 52:04.688 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
close our eyes and all pretend
to be an illustrator.

52:04.721 --> 52:10.827 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I guide them through a series of
visual things
that they're experiencing
through their imagination.

52:10.861 --> 52:16.099 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, when I did "A Boy and a
Jaguar," I had
them experience the jungle, and
they jump

52:16.133 --> 52:20.737 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
into a lake, and then they look
in the lake,
and what's reflected back to
them is the face

52:20.770 --> 52:22.539 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
of a jaguar.

52:22.572 --> 52:26.009 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There was this kid in the back
of the room
that was really loud and rowdy,
didn't want

52:26.042 --> 52:27.544 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
anything to do with me.

52:27.577 --> 52:31.381 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And he raised his hand and he
said, "I didn't
know that I could go there."

52:31.414 --> 52:36.653 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
That's the meaning of empathy, a
story that's
not your own that you can step
inside of.

52:36.686 --> 52:38.221 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
That's empathy.

52:38.255 --> 52:42.893 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
My family, in terms of how they
have responded
to my work, it's so practical.

52:42.926 --> 52:46.596 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You know, it has to do with
like, is that
paying you?

52:46.630 --> 52:50.834 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I have long ago understood that
that's not
where the gold is.

52:50.867 --> 52:55.138 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
You know, you will chase that
forever, and
then, at the end of your life,
you think,

52:55.172 --> 52:56.540 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
